WEBVTT

00:00:11.870 --> 00:00:13.750
Good morning, everyone.

00:00:13.850 --> 00:00:17.660
Welcome to another great day of WWDC.

00:00:17.880 --> 00:00:20.600
And thanks for spending your
morning with the books team.

00:00:20.670 --> 00:00:21.800
My name's Casey.

00:00:21.840 --> 00:00:23.840
I'm the engineering manager
for the iBooksstore.

00:00:23.840 --> 00:00:29.230
And one of my jobs is to develop
technology that will enable

00:00:29.230 --> 00:00:35.090
you to create books that people
are going to just love to read.

00:00:35.330 --> 00:00:39.340
So to help you with that,
today my colleagues and I are going

00:00:39.340 --> 00:00:45.240
to teach you how to create interactive
books using EPUB 3 and JavaScript.

00:00:45.810 --> 00:00:49.510
Before we jump into the technology
behind EPUB and JavaScript though,

00:00:49.580 --> 00:00:53.060
I'm going to run through real quickly
where we've been since last year.

00:00:53.070 --> 00:00:56.000
So first,
I'll recap last year's iBook session,

00:00:56.000 --> 00:01:00.410
and then I'm going to explain to you and
really share with you some of the cool

00:01:00.410 --> 00:01:02.890
new things we've added since last year.

00:01:03.540 --> 00:01:08.290
So, at last year's iBook session,
we showed you how to use EPUB 2 to

00:01:08.290 --> 00:01:13.340
create two different formats of books,
flowing and fixed layout.

00:01:13.340 --> 00:01:16.340
And as a reminder,
a flowing book is a book where

00:01:16.380 --> 00:01:18.540
the reader can resize the text.

00:01:18.540 --> 00:01:22.660
And in fact, the text in that document
is one long document,

00:01:22.660 --> 00:01:25.860
kind of like a web page,
that iBooks then neatly

00:01:25.860 --> 00:01:28.280
divides into individual pages.

00:01:29.000 --> 00:01:32.960
In contrast to that,
a fixed layout book is used when

00:01:32.960 --> 00:01:35.370
you want a very precise design.

00:01:35.370 --> 00:01:41.370
It has full-bleed images and
text that overlaps those images.

00:01:41.660 --> 00:01:44.950
For both of these formats,
you can embed audio and video

00:01:45.100 --> 00:01:47.800
using the HTML5 elements.

00:01:47.860 --> 00:01:50.540
And all of this was covered
in last year's session.

00:01:50.590 --> 00:01:53.300
In addition to that,
really my favorite moment from

00:01:53.300 --> 00:01:57.460
last year was when I got to
introduce to you Read Aloud.

00:01:57.590 --> 00:02:01.830
Read Aloud is a technology that
allows you to sync a narrator's

00:02:01.830 --> 00:02:06.800
voice with the text of your book
so that individual words light

00:02:06.980 --> 00:02:10.590
up as that audio is read aloud.

00:02:10.750 --> 00:02:12.600
Now,
if you missed last year's iBooks session,

00:02:12.600 --> 00:02:13.140
don't worry.

00:02:13.140 --> 00:02:16.200
It is available for download
on the Apple Developer Center.

00:02:16.200 --> 00:02:19.350
And if you're new to EPUB,
you can pick this technology

00:02:19.430 --> 00:02:20.780
up really quickly.

00:02:20.780 --> 00:02:24.300
And if you need more of a foundation,
definitely download last year's session.

00:02:26.940 --> 00:02:30.630
So since I last talked to you,
since last year,

00:02:30.740 --> 00:02:33.320
iBooks has been really busy.

00:02:34.070 --> 00:02:39.310
We are the first reading
system to support EPUB 3.

00:02:39.450 --> 00:02:43.090
And EPUB 3 support in itself,
let me tell you, it made for a busy year.

00:02:43.400 --> 00:02:45.230
But Apple didn't stop there.

00:02:45.230 --> 00:02:49.450
In January of this year,
Apple released iBooks Author.

00:02:49.460 --> 00:02:53.950
iBooks Author is a free app available
from the Mac App Store that makes

00:02:53.950 --> 00:02:56.320
it easy for anybody to make a book.

00:02:56.440 --> 00:03:00.510
It combines the simplicity of
copy and paste and drag and drop,

00:03:00.510 --> 00:03:04.620
along with some really creative
layout tools that makes it quick

00:03:04.880 --> 00:03:08.640
and easy to make some really
beautiful books for the iPad.

00:03:10.070 --> 00:03:13.470
So this year,
iBooks brings you EPUB 3 and iBooks

00:03:13.470 --> 00:03:17.720
Author to give you some really
great development tools for getting

00:03:17.870 --> 00:03:19.910
your books into the iBooks store.

00:03:20.110 --> 00:03:21.840
And I mean you in particular.

00:03:22.000 --> 00:03:25.040
So Apple developers,
you are a unique group.

00:03:25.150 --> 00:03:29.080
You have a more technological
background than just the average Joe.

00:03:29.220 --> 00:03:34.220
And that puts you in an especially
advantageous position for creating

00:03:34.220 --> 00:03:36.630
some really beautiful books.

00:03:36.840 --> 00:03:40.500
So yesterday, my colleague Charles demoed
iBooks Author.

00:03:40.620 --> 00:03:43.600
Today,
some more colleagues and I are going

00:03:43.600 --> 00:03:49.440
to show you how to put your technical
skills to use to create some interactive,

00:03:49.640 --> 00:03:52.250
engaging books using EPUB 3.

00:03:54.000 --> 00:03:55.700
And so you have options.

00:03:55.840 --> 00:03:58.300
When do you want to make an EPUB?

00:03:58.320 --> 00:04:01.140
Well, iBooks is actually a really
incredible platform for EPUB,

00:04:01.140 --> 00:04:04.880
and that's because we support
flowing and fixed layout,

00:04:04.890 --> 00:04:08.040
media like images, audio, and video.

00:04:08.070 --> 00:04:12.190
You can include your own fonts,
and you can make an interactive book,

00:04:12.240 --> 00:04:14.020
which we'll show you today.

00:04:14.110 --> 00:04:18.760
You can also create a read aloud book
to sync that audio with the text.

00:04:19.160 --> 00:04:23.380
And your single EPUB is
supported on the iPad,

00:04:23.380 --> 00:04:25.810
the iPhone, and the iPod Touch.

00:04:25.990 --> 00:04:28.790
So that's millions of devices
that are out there that are

00:04:28.880 --> 00:04:30.190
ready to read your book.

00:04:32.400 --> 00:04:38.600
Also, EPUB uses standard technologies
like HTML and CSS and JavaScript.

00:04:38.910 --> 00:04:42.360
So if you already have these skills,
you are more than halfway

00:04:42.360 --> 00:04:43.980
there to making a book.

00:04:44.020 --> 00:04:49.210
And finally, EPUB is open standard,
just like HTML and CSS,

00:04:49.350 --> 00:04:53.390
which means an EPUB can be
read across multiple platforms.

00:04:54.220 --> 00:04:58.900
In other words,
because EPUB uses web technologies,

00:04:59.020 --> 00:05:02.290
you can create a book
that's customizable,

00:05:02.290 --> 00:05:04.270
adaptable, and open.

00:05:04.380 --> 00:05:08.830
It gives you the ability to
create a single book for nearly

00:05:08.830 --> 00:05:13.810
any type of book that can be
read on many different devices.

