00:15:17.880 --> 00:15:23.570
And that figure 1 has a link that
points to chapter 1.xhtml with a

00:15:23.580 --> 00:15:26.790
fragment identifier of figure 1.

00:15:26.790 --> 00:15:31.080
And that's because our figure 1
exists within the chapter 1 document.

00:15:31.080 --> 00:15:36.580
So this link will then go and reference
a figure 1 ID within that document.

00:15:36.580 --> 00:15:39.280
So that is the basic structure.

00:15:39.580 --> 00:15:43.030
So you have your table of contents,
it's HTML list with

00:15:43.050 --> 00:15:44.920
the HTML5 nav element.

00:15:44.920 --> 00:15:49.920
And you use this same nav
structure to create landmarks.

00:15:50.600 --> 00:15:59.300
A landmarks replaces EPUB 2's guide,
and its job is to identify

00:15:59.300 --> 00:15:59.300
key files within your book.

00:15:59.850 --> 00:16:03.680
So it is essentially providing a
map to the structure of your book.

00:16:03.830 --> 00:16:08.470
And the iBooksStore will reference
the landmarks when we're cutting

00:16:08.470 --> 00:16:09.660
the sample for your book.

00:16:09.870 --> 00:16:13.470
So as a reminder,
that sample is the free sample that

00:16:13.470 --> 00:16:18.050
